National Treasury is considering an additional R7 billion ($463 million) equity injection for state-owned Land Bank as part of the national budgeting process, the Treasury told Reuters. The Treasury said that an assessment had showed that further guarantees were an inappropriate instrument to use to support the agriculture-focused lender and that equity was required. It added that more information on the R7 billion required by the Land Bank would be made available during the 2021 Budget, which is due in February. Subscribe for full access to all our share and unit trust data tools, our award-winning articles, and support quality journalism in the process. You will be redirected to a checkout page.
